{"title_page": "Araku Valley", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Araku Valley\n| native_name                     = \n| other_name                      = \n| settlement_type                 = Hill Station\n| image_skyline                   = ARAKU VALLEY.jpg\n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| nickname                        = Andhra Ooty\n| map_alt                         = \n| map_caption                     = \n| pushpin_map                     = India Andhra Pradesh\n| pushpin_label_position          = left\n| pushpin_map_alt                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = \n| coordinates                     = {{coord|18.3333|N|82.8667|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = [[India]]\n| subdivision_type1               = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Andhra Pradesh]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Visakhapatnam district|Visakhapatnam]]\n| established_title               = <!-- Establishedh;;o;ooih-->\n| established_date                = \n| founder                         = \n| named_for                       = \n| government_type                 = \n| governing_body                  = \n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_rank                       = \n| area_total_km2                  = \n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = 910\n| population_total                = 56,674\n| population_as_of                = 2011\n| population_rank                 = \n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| population_demonym              = \n| population_footnotes            = \n| demographics_type1              = Languages\n| demographics1_title1            = Official\n| demographics1_info1             = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code                     = 531 149\n| area_code_type                  = Telephone code\n| area_code                       = 08936\n| registration_plate              = AP\n| blank1_name_sec1                = [[Vidhan Sabha]] constituency\n| blank1_info_sec1                = [[Araku Valley (ST) (Assembly constituency)|Araku Valley]]\n| blank2_name_sec1                = [[Lok Sabha]] constituency\n| blank2_info_sec1                = [[Araku (ST) (Lok Sabha constituency)|Araku]]\n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n| official_name                   = \n| Member of Parliament            = Goddeti Madhavi\n| Member of Legislative Assembly  = Setty Palgonna\n}}\n\n'''Araku Valley''' is a hill station in [[Visakhapatnam district]] in the Indian state of [[Andhra Pradesh]], lying 111&nbsp;km west of [[Visakhapatnam]] city. This place is often referred to as ''Ooty of Andhra''. It is a valley in the Eastern Ghats inhabited by different tribes.\n\n==Geography==\nAraku is located in the [[Eastern Ghats]] about {{convert|114|km}} from [[Visakhapatnam]], close to the [[Odisha]] state border. The Anantagiri and Sunkarimetta Reserved Forest, which are part of Araku Valley, are rich in biodiversity and are mined for [[bauxite]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Cheated for bauxite|url=http://www.downtoearth.org.in/coverage/cheated-for-bauxite-35668|accessdate=27 March 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180630085127/http://www.downtoearth.org.in/coverage/cheated-for-bauxite-35668|archive-date=30 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Galikonda hill rising to a height of {{convert|5000|ft|m}} is amongst the highest peaks in Andhra Pradesh. The average rainfall is {{convert|1700|mm}}, the bulk of which is received during June\u2013October.<ref name=\"need\">{{cite report|url=http://www.indiaenvironmentportal.org.in/files/Need%20for%20conservation%20of%20biodiversity%20in%20Araku%20Valley.pdf|title=Need for conservation of biodiversity in Araku Valley, Andhra Pradesh|access-date=28 October 2017}}</ref>\nThe altitude is about 1300 m above the sea level. The valley spreads around 36&nbsp;km.<ref>{{cite web|title=Araku Valley|url=http://www.aptdc.gov.in/special-tours/araku_valley.html|website=www.aptdc.gov.in|accessdate=25 November 2017|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171115233233/http://www.aptdc.gov.in/special-tours/araku_valley.html|archive-date=15 November 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Economy==\n\n[[Coffee]] was first introduced in [[Eastern Ghats]] of [[Andhra Pradesh]] in 1898 by British in Pamuleru valley in [[East Godavari district]]. Subsequently, it spread over to Araku Valley in the early 19th century. After independence, the [[Andhra Pradesh Forest Department]] developed coffee plantations in the valley. In 1956, [[Coffee Board of India|Coffee Board]] appointed Andhra Pradesh Girijan Cooperative Corporation Limited (GCC) for promoting coffee plantations in the valley through local tribal farmers.{{clarification needed|date=July 2019}} In 1985, the plantations were handed to A.P. Forest Development Corporation and GCC promoted Girijan Coop. Plantation Development Corporation (GCPDC) exclusively to develop coffee plantations in tribal areas. All the plantations developed by GCC and GCPDC were handed over to the tribal farmers at two acres per family.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.apgirijan.com/|title=AP Girijan|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n\nAraku Valley is also an unexplored tourist destination \n\n1. Chaparai Waterfalls\n \n2. Padmapuram Botanical Garden\n\n3. Araku Tribal Museum\n\n4. Borra Caves\n\n5. TYDA jungle bells resorts \n\n6. Dhumuku hill view point \n\n7. Ananthagiri Borra caves \n\n\n\nBest time to visit Araku Valley is between December to February.\n\n==Transport==\n\nAraku is connected through both rail and road to Visakhapatnam. [[Araku railway station]] is located on the [[Kothavalasa]]-[[Kirandul]] railway line of Visakhapatnam division of the [[East Coast Railway]], on the [[Indian Railways]] network.\nRTC Buses to Visakhapatnam every half an hour\n\n==In popular culture==\n[[Cinema of Andhra Pradesh|Tollywood]] films including [[Happy Days (2007 film)|''Happy Days'']], [[Katha (2009 film)|''Katha'']], [[Darling (2010 film)|''Darling'']], [[Life Is Beautiful (2012 film)|''Life Is Beautiful'']] and ''[[Parugu]]'' were shot in Araku.{{citation needed|date=July 2019}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Araku Valley}}\n{{Wikivoyage|Aruku Valley}}\n* [http://indiatourism.ws/andhra_pradesh/aptdc/araku_valley/ Araku Valley] Pictures of Tribal museum, horticulture nursery, tribal dancing & Borra caves\n*[http://www.realbharat.org/7-best-places-to-visit-in-araku-valley-for-a-wonderful-weekend-getaway/ Katiki Water Falls], Chaparai Water Cascade\n\n[[Category:Valleys of India]]\n[[Category:Hill stations in Andhra Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Andhra Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Landforms of Andhra Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Geography of Visakhapatnam district]]\n[[Category:Uttarandhra]]\n[[Lesgislative Assembly]]\n*2009-2014 - Siveri Soma\n*2014-2018 - Kidari Sarveswara Rao\n*2019-     -Chetti Phalguna\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Araku Valley\n| native_name                     = \n| other_name                      = \n| settlement_type                 = Hill Station\n| image_skyline                   = ARAKU VALLEY.jpg\n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| nickname                        = Andhra Ooty\n| map_alt                         = \n| map_caption                     = \n| pushpin_map                     = India Andhra Pradesh\n| pushpin_label_position          = left\n| pushpin_map_alt                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = \n| coordinates                     = {{coord|18.3333|N|82.8667|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = [[India]]\n| subdivision_type1               = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Andhra Pradesh]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Visakhapatnam district|Visakhapatnam]]\n| established_title               = <!-- Establishedh;;o;ooih-->\n| established_date                = \n| founder                         = \n| named_for                       = \n| government_type                 = \n| governing_body                  = \n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_rank                       = \n| area_total_km2                  = \n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = 910\n| population_total                = 56,674\n| population_as_of                = 2011\n| population_rank                 = \n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| population_demonym              = \n| population_footnotes            = \n| demographics_type1              = Languages\n| demographics1_title1            = Official\n| demographics1_info1             = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code                     = 531 149\n| area_code_type                  = Telephone code\n| area_code                       = 08936\n| registration_plate              = AP\n| blank1_name_sec1                = [[Vidhan Sabha]] constituency\n| blank1_info_sec1                = [[Araku Valley (ST) (Assembly constituency)|Araku Valley]]\n| blank2_name_sec1                = [[Lok Sabha]] constituency\n| blank2_info_sec1                = [[Araku (ST) (Lok Sabha constituency)|Araku]]\n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n| official_name                   = \n| Member of Parliament            = Goddeti Madhavi\n| Member of Legislative Assembly  = Setty Palgonna\n}}\n\n'''Araku Valley''' is a hill station in [[Visakhapatnam district]] in the Indian state of [[Andhra Pradesh]], lying 111&nbsp;km west of [[Visakhapatnam]] city. This place is often referred to as ''Ooty of Andhra''. It is a valley in the Eastern Ghats inhabited by different tribes.\n\n==Geography==\nAraku is located in the [[Eastern Ghats]] about {{convert|114|km}} from [[Visakhapatnam]], close to the [[Odisha]] state border. The Anantagiri and Sunkarimetta Reserved Forest, which are part of Araku Valley, are rich in biodiversity and are mined for [[bauxite]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Cheated for bauxite|url=http://www.downtoearth.org.in/coverage/cheated-for-bauxite-35668|accessdate=27 March 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180630085127/http://www.downtoearth.org.in/coverage/cheated-for-bauxite-35668|archive-date=30 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Galikonda hill rising to a height of {{convert|5000|ft|m}} is amongst the highest peaks in Andhra Pradesh. The average rainfall is {{convert|1700|mm}}, the bulk of which is received during June\u2013October.<ref name=\"need\">{{cite report|url=http://www.indiaenvironmentportal.org.in/files/Need%20for%20conservation%20of%20biodiversity%20in%20Araku%20Valley.pdf|title=Need for conservation of biodiversity in Araku Valley, Andhra Pradesh|access-date=28 October 2017}}</ref>\nThe altitude is about 1300 m above the sea level. The valley spreads around 36&nbsp;km.<ref>{{cite web|title=Araku Valley|url=http://www.aptdc.gov.in/special-tours/araku_valley.html|website=www.aptdc.gov.in|accessdate=25 November 2017|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171115233233/http://www.aptdc.gov.in/special-tours/araku_valley.html|archive-date=15 November 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Economy==\n\n[[Coffee]] was first introduced in [[Eastern Ghats]] of [[Andhra Pradesh]] in 1898 by British in Pamuleru valley in [[East Godavari district]]. Subsequently, it spread over to Araku Valley in the early 19th century. After independence, the [[Andhra Pradesh Forest Department]] developed coffee plantations in the valley. In 1956, [[Coffee Board of India|Coffee Board]] appointed Andhra Pradesh Girijan Cooperative Corporation Limited (GCC) for promoting coffee plantations in the valley through local tribal farmers.{{clarification needed|date=July 2019}} In 1985, the plantations were handed to A.P. Forest Development Corporation and GCC promoted Girijan Coop. Plantation Development Corporation (GCPDC) exclusively to develop coffee plantations in tribal areas. All the plantations developed by GCC and GCPDC were handed over to the tribal farmers at two acres per family.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.apgirijan.com/|title=AP Girijan|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n\nAraku Valley is also an unexplored tourist destination \n\n1. Chaparai Waterfalls\n\n2. Ananthagiri Hills for hiking and trekking. \n\n3. Padmapuram Botanical Garden\n\n4. Araku Tribal Museum\n\n5. Borra Caves\n\nBest time to visit Araku Valley is between December to February.\n\n==Transport==\n\nAraku is connected through both rail and road to Visakhapatnam. [[Araku railway station]] is located on the [[Kothavalasa]]-[[Kirandul]] railway line of Visakhapatnam division of the [[East Coast Railway]], on the [[Indian Railways]] network.\nRTC Buses to Visakhapatnam every half an hour\n\n==In popular culture==\n[[Cinema of Andhra Pradesh|Tollywood]] films including [[Happy Days (2007 film)|''Happy Days'']], [[Katha (2009 film)|''Katha'']], [[Darling (2010 film)|''Darling'']], [[Life Is Beautiful (2012 film)|''Life Is Beautiful'']] and ''[[Parugu]]'' were shot in Araku.{{citation needed|date=July 2019}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Araku Valley}}\n{{Wikivoyage|Aruku Valley}}\n* [http://indiatourism.ws/andhra_pradesh/aptdc/araku_valley/ Araku Valley] Pictures of Tribal museum, horticulture nursery, tribal dancing & Borra caves\n*[http://www.realbharat.org/7-best-places-to-visit-in-araku-valley-for-a-wonderful-weekend-getaway/ Katiki Water Falls], Chaparai Water Cascade\n\n[[Category:Valleys of India]]\n[[Category:Hill stations in Andhra Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Andhra Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Landforms of Andhra Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Geography of Visakhapatnam district]]\n[[Category:Uttarandhra]]\n[[Lesgislative Assembly]]\n*2009-2014 - Siveri Soma\n*2014-2018 - Kidari Sarveswara Rao\n*2019-     -Chetti Phalguna\n", "name_user": "Seshasai1998", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eEconomy", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Araku_Valley"}
