es/default.stm Kosovo fact files] [[BBC News]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20000815075301/http://www.cnn.com/SPECIALS/1998/10/kosovo/ Focus on Kosovo] [[CNN]]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCHTK-2W11Vh1V4uwofOfR4w/search?query=kosovo Kosovo War on AP Video Archive] [[Associated Press]]\n\n===Maps===\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20040111054136/http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/kosovo.html Maps of Kosovo, Perry\u2013Casta\u00f1eda Library Map Collection]\n\n{{Post-Cold War European conflicts}}\n{{Kosovo topics}}\n{{Yugoslavia topics}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Kosovo War| ]]\n[[Category:1998 in Kosovo]]\n[[Category:1999 in Kosovo]]\n[[Category:History of Kosovo]]\n[[Category:Ethnic cleansing in Europe]]\n[[Category:Albania\u2013Serbia relations]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 1998]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 1999]]\n", "text_old": "{{For|other combat operations in the Kosovo region|Battle of Kosovo (disambiguation)}}\n{{pp-vandalism|small=yes|expiry=indefinite}}\n{{Use British English|date=November 2014}}\n{{Infobox military conflict\n| conflict          = Kosovo War\n| partof            = the [[Yugoslav Wars]]<ref>[[#Thomas|Thomas (2006)]], p. 47</ref>\n| image             = Kosovo War header.jpg\n| image_size        = 300px\n| caption           = '''Clockwise from top-left:''' Yugoslav general staff headquarters damaged by [[NATO]] air strikes; a [[Zastava Koral]] buried under rubble caused by NATO air strikes; memorial to local [[Kosovo Liberation Army|KLA]] commanders; a [[United States Air Force|USAF]] [[F-15E Strike Eagle|F-15E]] taking off from [[Aviano Air Base]]\n| date              = February 1998&nbsp;\u2013 11 June 1999<br />\n| place             = [[Autonomous Province of Kosovo and Metohija|Kosovo]] (then part of [[Serbia and Montenegro|Yugoslavia]]) and [[Albania]] {{small|(Albanian & OSCE Claim)}}<ref>{{cite news|url=https://articles.latimes.com/1999/apr/14/news/mn-27375|title=Yugoslav Troops Said to Cross Into Albania|work=Los Angeles Times|date=1999-04-14|accessdate=2012-02-20|first=John|last=Daniszewski}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/war-in-the-balkans-serbs-enter-albania-and-burn-village-1087030.html|title=War In The Balkans: Serbs enter Albania and burn village|work=The Independent|date=1999-04-14|accessdate=2012-02-20|location=London|first1=Emma|last1=Daly}}</ref><ref>https://fas.org/irp/threat/terrorism/sup6.pdf</ref><ref>http://www.wrmea.com/backissues/0799/9907060.html</ref>\n| territory         = No legal changes to Yugoslav borders according to the [[United Nations Security Council Resolution 1244|Resolution 1244]], but effective political and economic separation of [[Autonomous Province of Kosovo and Metohija|Kosovo]] from [[Serbia and Montenegro|Yugoslavia]] due to being placed under [[UNMIK|UN administration]] and subsequent declaration of independence\n| result            = [[Kumanovo Treaty]]\n*Yugoslav forces pull out of Kosovo\n*[[United Nations Security Council Resolution 1244|United Nations Resolution 1244]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/1999/06/10/MN82284.DTL|title=Yugoslav, NATO Generals Sign Peace Agreement for Kosovo / Alliance will end air campaign when Serbian troops pull out|work=San Francisco Chronicle|date=1999-06-10|accessdate=2012-02-20|first1=Valerie|last1=Reitman|first2=Paul|last2=Richter|first3=John-Thor|last3=Dahlburg}}</ref>\n*Return of [[Kosovo Albanians|Albanian]] refugees\n*Expulsion of over half of the [[Kosovo Serbs|Serb]] and other non-Albanian civilians{{#tag:ref|<ref>{{cite web|title=Abuses against Serbs and Roma in the new Kosovo |url=https://www.hrw.org/reports/1999/kosov2/|publisher=[[Human Rights Watch]]|date=August 1999}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=After Yugoslavia: Identities and Politics Within the Successor States |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wkQ3I6GyClEC&pg=PA29 |date=2012|p=30|isbn=9780230201316 |last1=Hudson |first1=Robert |last2=Bowman |first2=Glenn }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Kosovo Crisis Update|url=http://www.unhcr.org/3ae6b80f2c.html|publisher=[[United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees|UNHCR]]|date=August 4, 1999}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Forced Expulsion of Kosovo Roma, Ashkali and Egyptians from OSCE Participated state to Kosovo |url=http://www.osce.org/odihr/21342?download=true|publisher=[[Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe|OSCE]]|date=October 6, 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Siobh\u00e1n Wills|title=Protecting Civilians: The Obligations of Peacekeepers|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QoqQ7kBrlSAC&pg=PA219|accessdate=24 February 2013|date=26 February 2009|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-953387-9|page=219}}</ref>|group=lower-alpha}}\n*[[Kosovo Liberation Army|KLA]] veterans join the [[Liberation Army of Pre\u0161evo, Medve\u0111a and Bujanovac|U\u00c7PMB]], starting the [[Insurgency in the Pre\u0161evo Valley|Pre\u0161evo insurgency]]\n*[[Overthrow of Slobodan Milo\u0161evi\u0107|Bulldozer Revolution]] in 2000\n| combatant1        = [[File:UCK KLA.png|25px|alt=Kosovo Liberation Army]] [[Kosovo Liberation Army|KLA]]\n\n[[File:Flag of The Republic of Kosova (1991\u20131999).svg|25px|alt=Republic of Kosova]] [[Republic of Kosova]]<br /> (Until 1999)\n----\n{{Collapsible list\n|bullets = yes\n|title = {{Flag|NATO|size=23px}}\n|{{flag|Belgium|size=23px}}\n|{{flag|Canada|size=23px}}\n|{{flag|Denmark|size=23px}}\n|{{flag|France|size=23px}}\n|{{flag|Germany|size=23px}}\n|{{flag|Italy|size=23px}}\n|{{flag|Luxembourg|size=23px}}\n|{{flag|Netherlands|size=23px}}\n|{{flag|Norway|size=23px}}\n|{{flag|Portugal|size=23px}}\n|{{flag|Spain|size=23px}}\n|{{flag|Turkey|size=23px}}\n|{{flag|United Kingdom|size=23px}}\n|{{flag|United States|1960|size=23px}}<ref name=\"planken1\">{{cite web|url=http://planken.org/balkans/allied-force/statistics|title=The Balkans/Allied Force: Statistics|publisher=planken.org|accessdate=2012-02-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130619005117/http://planken.org/balkans/allied-force/statistics|archive-date=2013-06-19|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n}}\n<!-- please don't insert \"volunteers\" of any sort, as they are not combatant authorities -->| combatant2        = {{flag|Serbia and Montenegro|name=Yugoslavia}}\n<!-- please don't insert \"volunteers\" of any sort, as they are not combatant authorities -->| commander1        = [[File:UCK KLA.png|25px|alt=Logo of the Kosovo Liberation Army]] [[Adem Jashari]]{{KIA}}<br />\n[[File:UCK KLA.png|25px|alt=Logo of the Kosovo Liberation Army]] [[Hashim Tha\u00e7i]]<br />\n[[File:UCK KLA.png|25px|alt=Logo of the Kosovo Liberation Army]] Bilall Syla<br />\n[[File:UCK KLA.png|25px|alt=Logo of the Kosovo Liberation Army]] [[Ham\u00ebz Jashari]]{{KIA}}<br />\n[[File:UCK KLA.png|25px|alt=Logo of the Kosovo Liberation Army]] [[Sylejman Selimi]]<br />\n[[File:UCK KLA.png|25px|alt=Logo of the Kosovo Liberation Army]] [[Ramush Haradinaj]]<br />\n[[File:UCK KLA.png|25px|alt=Logo of the Kosovo Liberation Army]] [[Agim \u00c7eku]]<br />\n----\n{{flagicon|NATO}} [[Wesley Clark]]\n----\n{{flagicon|Albania}} Kudusi Lama <ref name=KL>{{citation|last=Katamaj|first=Halil|year=2002|title=Kudusi Lama, War General of division of Kukes, during the Kosovo war|location=Tiran\u00eb|publisher=Mokra|isbn=978-99927-781-0-4}}{{page needed|date=May 2012}}</ref>\n| commander2        = {{flagicon|Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|1992}} [[Slobodan Milo\u0161evi\u0107]]<br />\n{{Flagdeco|Serbia and Montenegro}} [[Dragoljub Ojdani\u0107]]<br />\n{{Flagdeco|Serbia and Montenegro}} [[Neboj\u0161a Pavkovi\u0107]]<br />\n{{Flagdeco|Serbia and Montenegro}} [[Vlastimir \u0110or\u0111evi\u0107]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-12563330|title=BBC News&nbsp;\u2013 Serbian Vlastimir Djordjevic jailed over Kosovo murders|work=BBC News|date=2011-02-24|accessdate=2012-05-06}}</ref><br />\n{{Flagdeco|Serbia and Montenegro}} [[Vladimir Lazarevi\u0107]]<ref name=\"setimes2006\">{{cite web|url=h